   - So the gcd becomes $\gcd(14n + 3, 7n + 1)$

2. Compute $\gcd(14n + 3, 7n + 1)$:
   - $14n + 3 = 2 \cdot (7n + 1) + 1$
   - So the gcd becomes $\gcd(7n + 1, 1)$

